":"Grisham","meanings":["English: variant of   Gresham  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William deBraunche of Gresham was born in 1086, his father, Richard de Braunche II, was 37 and his mother, Nine de Gresham, was 19. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1086–":"1086–Surnud","1086–Male":"1086–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1101–Male":"1101–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1050–1101":"1050–1101","1066–Female":"1066–Surnud","1090":"1090","1101":"1101","1066":"1066","1175":"1175","1086":"1086","1050":"1050"},"fi":{"1086–":"1086–Kuollut","1086–Male":"1086–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1101–Male":"1101–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1050–1101":"1050–1101","1066–Female":"1066–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1101":"1101","1066":"1066","1175":"1175","1086":"1086","1050":"1050"},"fr":{"1086–":"1086–Décédé","1086–Male":"1086–Décédé","1090–Male":"1090–Décédé","1101–Male":"1101–Décédé","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1050–1101":"1050–1101","1066–Female":"1066–Décédée","1090":"1090","1101":"1101","1066":"1066","1175":"1175","1086":"1086","1050":"1050","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir William deBraunche of Gresham est né en 1086, son père, Richard de Braunche II, avait 37 ans et